                    "goals": [
                        "Maintain naval superiority in the Channel and North Sea; keep sea lanes safe for commerce and leverage.",
                        "Avoid premature continental entanglement; use fleets to shape balance-of-power rather than deep land commitments.",
                        "Keep a flexible, provisional understanding with France to deny early Franco-German or Franco-Russian advantage.",
                        "Prevent Germany from establishing uncontested North Sea/Baltic control; use diplomatic pressure to deter KIE->NTH/BER->DKK moves.",
                        "Secure at least one additional supply center by end of 1902 (prefer targets in Scandinavia or Low Countries) while preserving LON/EDI/LVP.",
