                    "full_private_diary": [
                        "[S1901M] Provisional outreach completed. With FRANCE: I proposed a Channel demilitarisation \u2014 I will keep LON->ENG and avoid pressing into BEL/PIC/PICARDY in return for France avoiding BRE->ENG and not contesting the Channel this turn; France response is cautious but tentatively positive (treat as provisional). With GERMANY: I signalled that I do not intend to enter the Baltic if Germany avoids an immediate NTH/DEN thrust; Germany gave no firm commitment (treat as unconfirmed). Russia/Italy/Austria/Turkey: no substantive commitments; I offered general neutrality and willingness to coordinate against any continental hegemon. Forecast: my planned fleet moves (F LON->ENG, F EDI->NTH) will contest the Channel and North Sea; any German move into NTH/DEN or French move into ENG will rapidly raise risk of Anglo-German or Anglo-French naval clashes \u2014 plan coalitions accordingly.\nIntent: Planned orders for S1901M: F LON -> ENG (will execute to occupy Channel and signal non-aggression if France holds her side); F EDI -> NTH (will execute to assert North Sea presence and deter German domination); A LVP -> YOR (will execute to keep an inland staging army). I intend to fulfil the provisional agreement with France as long as France does not move BRE->ENG or otherwise contest the Channel this turn. Contingency: if France immediately violates the Channel understanding, fallback is to defend LON/secure sea approaches and re-evaluate alliance with France next phase.",
                        "[S1901M] Provisional Channel demilitarisation held: France did not contest BRE->ENG this turn, so my F LON->ENG and F EDI->NTH executed as planned and A LVP->YOR kept a safe inland staging ground. No outright betrayals \u2014 I did not break the agreement; France proved tentatively reliable this phase. Germany remained non\u2011committal but also showed no immediate NTH/DEN thrust, reducing acute naval risk for now. No surprises in hostile action, but the silence from Berlin is a warning: untrustworthy until a clear pledge is made. Impact: Channel and North Sea presence preserved our naval leverage and protected LON/EDI/LVP. Lesson: maintain firm fleet posture and publicized movement forecasts to keep France aligned and deter German incursions; be ready to shift to defensive consolidation if France violates the truce."
                    ],
